WEBVTT

00:02:59.920 --> 00:03:01.496
and then to my joy she said,

00:03:01.520 --> 00:03:04.376
"If that's what you want to do,
and it means so much to you,

00:03:04.400 --> 00:03:05.656
then let's do it.

00:03:05.680 --> 00:03:08.656
Let's find ways to see if parent programs

00:03:08.680 --> 00:03:11.040
can be useful for families
in these contexts."

00:03:11.960 --> 00:03:14.856
So for the past five years,
myself and my colleagues --

00:03:14.880 --> 00:03:17.456
Prof. Calam and Dr. Kim Cartwright --

00:03:17.480 --> 00:03:19.696
have been working
on ways to support families

00:03:19.720 --> 00:03:21.920
that have experienced
war and displacement.

00:03:23.560 --> 00:03:26.976
Now, to know how to help families
that have been through conflict

00:03:27.000 --> 00:03:28.416
support their children,

00:03:28.440 --> 00:03:32.256
the first step must obviously be
to ask them what they're struggling with,